article.headline: Fla Atlantic 82, Campbell 59
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. (AP) -- Mike Bell had 22 points and added five blocks to lead Florida Atlantic to its first win of the season, an 82-59 victory over Campbell on Tuesday night. Bell also had five rebounds, but it was his 5-for-8 3-point shooting that led the Owls (1-4, 1-1 Atlantic Sun Conference) to the win. Florida Atlantic hit 11 shots from behind the arc compared to just three for the Camels (2-4, 0-1). Jimmy Bishop added 11 points for the Owls while Robert Williams and Lamar Moore each had 10. Kahleaf Watson had just four points but dished out 10 assists for Florida Atlantic . The Owls jumped out to a quick 14-4 lead less than five minutes in. Campbell cut the deficit to three with an 8-0 run with just under four minutes left in the half, but the Owls ended the half on an 11-1 run to take a 13-point lead. The Owls hit better than 53 percent from the field in the second half to pull away. Diego Aguiar led Campbell with 17 points while Maurice Latham finished with 13. Comerlee Poole added 11 rebounds for the Camels.
